    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim was to determine the knowledge attitudes, beliefs, and practices regarding HIV in a
      population of sex workers in French Guiana and in the Brazilian border town of Oiapoque. A
      standardized questionnaire was administered face to face to sex workers. Analysis of the
      questionnaires led to descriptive statistics. Multiple logistic regression models were
      computed to determine the predictors of condom use.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
